European Stocks, U.S. Futures Rise on G-7 Intervention; BHP Billiton Gains

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-18T08:04:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/european-stocks-u-s-futures-rise-on-g-7-intervention-bhp-billiton-gains.html
European stocks and U.S. index
futures advanced as the Group of Seven nations agreed to sell
the yen to ease concern that  Japan  will sink into recession
following the March 11 earthquake. Most Asian shares rose.  BHP Billiton Ltd. climbed 1.5 percent to 2,314.5 pence as
metal prices rose.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index gained 0.4 percent to 268.09 at
8:03 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  